{meta: title When It's Night Time In Nevada}
{meta: artist Sons of the Pioneers}
{meta: composer Richard W. Pascoe, Will Dulmage, H. O. Reilly Clint}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]When it's nighttime in [F]Nevada I'm [C]dreaming
Of the [G7]old days on the prairie and [C]you
I miss you when the [F]campfires are [C]gleaming
And I [D7]wonder if you miss me [G7]too
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I can [F]see the Great Divide and the [C]trails we used to ride
The [D7]only bit of heaven I [G7]knew
[C]When it's nighttime in [F]Nevada I'm [C]dreaming
Of the [G7]old days on the prairie and [C]you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I've been drifting [F]since we've rode the [C]ranges
Up [G7]to roaming when you went [C]away
With the love for [F]you that never [C]changes
I'm [D7]hoping we will meet again some[G7]day
{end_of_verse}

